manifest_analysis.title: Launch Mode of Activity (com.jerky.browser2.activities.OnboardingIncognitoActivity) is not standard.
manifest_analysis.desc: An Activity should not be having the launch mode attribute set to "singleTask/singleInstance" as it becomes root Activity and it is possible for other applications to read the contents of the calling Intent. So it is required to use the "standard" launch mode attribute when sensitive information is included in an Intent.
manifest_analysis.name: Launch Mode of Activity is not standard.

metadata.description: Query Database of SMS, Contacts etc
The App logs information. Sensitive information should never be logged.
metadata.cwe: CWE-532 Insertion of Sensitive Information into Log File

metadata.description: App can read/write to External Storage. Any App can read data written to External Storage.

metadata.cwe: CWE-312 Cleartext Storage of Sensitive Information
metadata.description: Files may contain hardcoded sensitive informations like usernames, passwords, keys etc.
The App uses ECB mode in Cryptographic encryption algorithm. ECB mode is known to be weak as it results in the same ciphertext for identical blocks of plaintext.
metadata.cwe: CWE-327 Use of a Broken or Risky Cryptographic Algorithm
CWE-327 Use of a Broken or Risky Cryptographic Algorithm
metadata.description: SHA-1 is a weak hash known to have hash collisions.
App uses SQLite Database and execute raw SQL query. Untrusted user input in raw SQL queries can cause SQL Injection. Also sensitive information should be encrypted and written to the database.
metadata.cwe: CWE-89 Improper Neutralization of Special Elements used in an SQL Command ('SQL Injection')

metadata.description: Insecure WebView Implementation. WebView ignores SSL Certificate errors and accept any SSL Certificate. This application is vulnerable to MITM attacks
This App copies data to clipboard. Sensitive data should not be copied to clipboard as other applications can access it.

FCS_RBG_EXT.1.1.choice: The application invoke platform-provided DRBG functionality for its cryptographic operations.

FCS_STO_EXT.1.1.choice: The application does not store any credentials to non-volatile memory.

FCS_CKM_EXT.1.1.choice: The application generate no asymmetric cryptographic keys.

FDP_DEC_EXT.1.1.choice: The application has access to ['network connectivity', 'location'].

FDP_DEC_EXT.1.2.choice: The application has access to no sensitive information repositories.

FDP_NET_EXT.1.1.choice: The application has user/application initiated network communications.

FDP_DAR_EXT.1.1.choice: The application implement functionality to encrypt sensitive data in non-volatile memory.

FMT_MEC_EXT.1.1.choice: The application invoke the mechanisms recommended by the platform vendor for storing and setting configuration options.

FTP_DIT_EXT.1.1.choice: The application does encrypt some transmitted data with HTTPS/TLS/SSH between itself and another trusted IT product.

FCS_RBG_EXT.2.1,FCS_RBG_EXT.2.2.choice: The application perform all deterministic random bit generation (DRBG) services in accordance with NIST Special Publication 800-90A using Hash_DRBG. The deterministic RBG is seeded by an entropy source that accumulates entropy from a platform-based DRBG and a software-based noise source, with a minimum of 256 bits of entropy at least equal to the greatest security strength (according to NIST SP 800-57) of the keys and hashes that it will generate.

FCS_COP.1.1(1).choice: The application perform encryption/decryption not in accordance with FCS_COP.1.1(1), AES-ECB mode is being used.

FCS_COP.1.1(2).choice: The application perform cryptographic hashing services in accordance with a specified cryptographic algorithm SHA-1/SHA-256/SHA-384/SHA-512 and message digest sizes 160/256/384/512 bits.

FCS_HTTPS_EXT.1.2.choice: The application implement HTTPS using TLS.

FCS_HTTPS_EXT.1.3.choice: The application notify the user and not establish the connection or request application authorization to establish the connection if the peer certificate is deemed invalid.

FIA_X509_EXT.1.1.choice: The application invoked platform-provided functionality to validate certificates in accordance with the following rules: ['The certificate path must terminate with a trusted CA certificate'].

FIA_X509_EXT.2.1.choice: The application use X.509v3 certificates as defined by RFC 5280 to support authentication for HTTPS , TLS.

FPT_TUD_EXT.2.1.choice: The application shall be distributed using the format of the platform-supported package manager.

strings: "personal_plea" : "I am an indie developer who is working full-time to build apps/services like Jerky to keep our internet free. It costs a lot to keep the servers going. Your subscription will help in keeping bread on the table and the servers alive. Thank you so much for your support! -steven"
"reading_mode_desc" : "Reading mode extracts the content so you can read without any distractions"
"closed_all_tabs_except_last" : "Closed all tabs except your current tab"
"if_you_like_contribute_more" : "If you like, you can contribute more. Thank YOU!"
"subscription_no_longer_active" : "Your subscription is no longer active. Please email the creator for more info on how to resubscribe."
"unlimited_tabs_desc" : "I refuse to cripple the browser with a pay wall. But for your support, I would like to open up the option of opening unlimited tabs. Hope that helps!"
"what_is_spirit_mode" : "Spirit mode enables a super-fast and private proxy tunnel (VPN) to privately browse websites while bypassing blocked websites at work or at home."
"u_sure_exit_app" : "Are you sure you want to exit the app?"
"average_1_tap" : "navigate Javelin with an average of 1 tap, and no more than 2 taps"

"enable_adblock_what_is_it" : "Jerky is the first Android browser to integrate Ad-Block natively, without a need for external apps or root permission. Enable Ad-Block to instantly enjoy websites ad-free."
"first_browser_w_adblock" : "Javelin will the first mobile browser that comes with a built-in ad-block."
"needs_at_least_android_version" : "Sorry! Adblock requires at least Android 3.0 and your device has a version older than that."
"you_can_gift_javelin_pro" : "Thank you so much for your support! I have another surprise for you! For your kind support, you can gift Javelin Pro (the full version) to 2 more friends for free!"
"can_browse_adfree" : "You can now browse ads-free! If you need to, you can always disable ad-block in Settings. Enjoy!"
"bypass_porn_filters_writeup" : "Enable spirit mode to instantly tunnel your traffic around your workplace or ISP so you can immediately regain access to blocked websites."

"license_desc" : "Javelin is licensed with Apache 2.0 (inherited from Lightning Browser). The code base was used as a foundation to extend and build upon. Since then, major chances include and are not limited to the UI, proxy feature, ad-block, gestures, readability mode, etc."
"flaticon_desc" : "Flaticon is a resource for flat icons."
"spirit_enabled_message" : "Your spirit mode is now enabled. To enable it, simply tap on the flying woman icon on the right of the address bar."
"every_cent" : "Every cent of your upgrade goes into the fight in making the web play nice for mobile."
"unable_to_complete_purchase" : "Unable to complete purchase, please try again later!"
"spirit_mode_activated" : "Spirit mode activated. Your browsing is now proxied, to be private and secure!"
"for_your_support" : "For your support, Here are 2 free copies of Javelin Pro, and some invites.."

"hi_steven" : "Hi! First of all, thank you for downloading Javelin, and I hope you LOVE it. As a technologist, then an indie developer, I'm building a browser that I'd use everyday. Your purchase of Javelin Pro will fund my daily living in improving Javelin for you. Thank you so much for your support!"
"ten_android_wear_invites" : "Additionally, the next 10 users who sign up via the gift link will also be the first private beta users of Javelin Browser for the Android Wear."
"permanently_incognito_writeup" : "Your web history is never saved and your cookies are always deleted. No one needs to know your surfing habits."
"super_fast_speeds_writeup" : "Jerky proxy servers are hosted on gigabit-line servers. Often or not, the Spirit will end up speeding up your download speeds."
"what_to_do_w_link" : "What do you want to do with this link?"
"faster_page_load_desc" : "Without having to load ads assets, pages now load faster."
"twofinger_swipe_right_tip" : "(TIP) You can easily switch between tabs by swiping left/right with 2 fingers."
"faster_page_load_writeup" : "Because you don't load ads (videos, images, webpages), webpages load way faster."
"unable_to_reach_server" : "Unable to reach server, please try again later!"
"change_homepage_writeup" : "By default, I've left in a beautiful homepage. But with Pro, you can change the homepage to any URL you like."
"access_blocked_sites_writeup" : "Access blocked sites securely and faster with a Smart Private Proxy Service hosted on a super-fast gigabit server."
"ten_invites_android_wear" : "10 INVITES FOR JAVELIN ON ANDROID WEAR"
"introducing_javelin_browser" : "Introducing Javelin Browser, a full browser based on Jerky browser (from your popular requests)."
"what_to_do_w_image" : "What would you like to do with this image?"

"give_it_a_shot" : "You have tried to claim Javelin Pro but it has already been claimed by at least 2 people before you. Why don't you give Javelin Free a shot and if you like it, you can upgrade to Javelin Pro. Thanks!"
"remove_bookmark" : "To remove a bookmark, tap and hold till the prompt to remove it appears."
"save_bandwidth_writeup" : "Mobile bandwidth is expensive. Don't waste those on ads. Block them."
"spirit_enabled_message_for_javelin" : "Your spirit mode is now enabled. You can enable Spirit mode anytime from the menu by swiping from the left edge."
"spirit_mode_deactivated" : "Spirit mode deactivated. You are now back to regular browsing."
"tap_n_hold_tooltip_desc" : "(TIP) To quickly preview and switch between all tabs, simply TAP AND HOLD on a tab."

"adblock_plus_desc" : "Just want to shout out to the guys at AdBlock Plus for their very wonderful and open-sourced work. Including their very famous ad filter list - Easylist, which is being used by Jerky for its built-in Adblock."
"unsplash_desc" : "Also to the wondrous photographer at Unsplash, for which I used one of his Creative Commons picture for the background image used in the homepage."
"block_all_ads_writeup" : "All external links are filtered with EasyList (ad filter). No scripts, images, or webpages from known ad hosts will be shown."
"snacktory_credits_desc" : "Snacktory is a readability clone in Java"

"fork_from_lightning" : "Jerky is forked and extended from a superb open-sourced project known as Lightning Browser by ACR Development. Thank you ACR development for liberally licensing the project and allow us (other devs) to build on top of your project rather than re-inventing the wheel and writing a whole new browser ourselves."
"now_in_incognito" : "You are now in Incognito mode. Your history, cookies and browsing data will not be stored."

"begun_android_wear" : "I have begun building Javelin browser for Android Wear. You can expect a stripped down version of websites with readable content accessible from voice-activated Google Search."
"first_for_android_wear" : "You will be FIRST to use Javelin on Android Wear devices"
"that_is" : "A truly mobile web in a browser that is"
"reading_mode_desc_2" : "One tap and Javelin will turn any content-heavy website into a simple page with beautiful typography for you to read, minus the obtrusive page elements."
"private_browsing_writeup" : "Hide your browsing habits from your workplace, nanny firewall, or even your big government by tunneling the traffic away from your destination."
"more_screen_estate_writeup" : "With the limited screen estate, you can now reclaim precious screen space from ads."
"password_protected_writeup" : "Prevent any snooping on your recent browsing activity, even if it is still active in your recently opened applications. Only you can open Javin."
"bookmarks_desc" : "Javelin browser will learn from your browsing history, and show the bookmarks when you need them, be in on a new tab, or while autocompleting your URL."
